<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-06T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-06T10:00:00-05:00" n="724" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d724">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/1178</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MIN1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Stockholm</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-06T16:00:00+01:00">
                                <hi rend="italic">November 6, 1914, 4 p.m.</hi>
                            </date>
                            <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 6 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>Considerable feeling here because British closing North Sea. Swedish
                            Government issued protest.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Minister</hi>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>